As a developer of DLG utilities, this guide is designed to aid you in
creating programs to work well with DLG Pro. Library functions are arranged
in a manner similar to the SAS/C library guide for your convenience.

  @{" Using this guide  " link "Using" 0} @{" Distribution      " link "Distribution" 0} @{" Copyright         " link "Copyright" 0}
  @{" Credits           " link "Credits" 0} @{" Contacts          " link "Contacts" 0} @{" Alphabetical Index" link "Index" 0}

The functions are arranged by category, for your convenience, and an
alphabetical index is included for an alternative method of locating the
desired function.

  @{"     PORT functions" link "Port_Funcs" 0} -- functions that address external ports.
  @{"     USER functions" link "User_Funcs" 0} -- functions that manipulate user data
  @{"STRUCTURE Functions" link "Struct Funcs" 0} -- manipulate structured data items
  @{"      I/O functions" link "IO Funcs" 0} -- user I/O functions
  @{"     TIME Functions" link "Time Funcs" 0} -- functions related to time
  @{"     FILE Functions" link "File Funcs" 0} -- functions that control file I/O
  @{"  LOGGING functions" link "Logging Funcs" 0} -- functions for logging and informing
  @{"   STRING functions" link "Ute Funcs" 0} -- strings and other things
  @{"BROADCAST Functions" link "BCST Funcs" 0} -- Broadcast to and from ports/users
  @{"     AREA functions" link "Area Funcs" 0} -- Manipulation of file and message areas
  @{"     EXEC functions" link "Exec Funcs" 0} -- call or use external programs
  @{"   SERIAL functions" link "Serial Funcs" 0} -- Control I/O on the serial port
  @{" RESOURCE functions" link "Resource Funcs" 0} -- Misc resources and structures

Along with the above functions, please see @{"format.c" link "format.c" 0} for routines that will
interface your program to DLG's internal print routines.
@endnode

