@node "BorrowArea()" "dlg.library/BorrowArea"

  NAME
    BorrowArea -- Lock an area for a short period of time

  SYNOPSIS
    result = BorrowArea(area,passwd,reason,pri,flags)
                        D0   A0     A1     D1  D2
    LONG BorrowArea(USHORT,char *,char *,char,UBYTE)

  FUNCTION
    Locks an area, but should only be used if the area will be locked
    for a very short period of time (a few seconds at most).

  INPUTS
    area   -- Number of the area to be locked.

    passwd -- Password to lock area with.

    reason -- Reason the area is being locked.

    pri    -- Priority for lock (-127 to 128).

    flags  -- As defined in @{"resman.h" link "include:dialog/resman.h/main" 85}.

  RESULT
    Error message as defined in @{"resman.h" link "include:dialog/resman.h/main" 68}.

  EXAMPLE
    result - BorrowArea(20,"MyPasswd","Doing something",0,MSGLOCK);

  NOTES
    An area should be entered (@{"EnterArea()" link "EnterArea()" 0}) before BorrowArea is used
    and the area must be released using FreeArea.

    An application is allowed to borrow an area even if there are
    other users (@{"EnterArea()" link "EnterArea()" 0}) in the area.

    Once an Area has been borrowed, all other BorrowArea calls will
    wait until the area is freed.  Pending BorrowAreas will be
    honored on a First-In, First-Out basis.

    Consider BorrowArea()/@{"FreeArea()" link "FreeArea()" 0} like the Amiga executive
    functions Forbid()/Permit().  Use BorrowArea()/@{"FreeArea()" link "FreeArea()" 0} _only_
    for short term locks.  Otherwise, users might think that the BBS
    has locked up.

    Never try to BorrowArea() the same area without doing a
    @{"FreeArea()" link "FreeArea()" 0} between the BorrowAreas.  Your program (and port) will
    hang.

    All of the DLG.Library functions that deal with message and file
    areas do their own BorrowArea/FreeArea, so you _must_ have freed
    the area before using them.

  BUGS

  SEE ALSO
    @{"LockArea()" link "LockArea()" 0}, @{"FreeArea()" link "FreeArea()" 0}, @{"EnterArea()" link "EnterArea()" 0}, @{"LeaveArea()" link "LeaveArea()" 0}
@endnode

